Explain how the ability to use video and audio on the web has evolved since the early 2000s.

Back in the days internet and browsers were alot slower and not as advanced as todays browsers and interent. Also the video formats would have been small and bad quailty. Now days we have faster internet and better browsers allowing us to have high res pics and video on our webpages giving use great capabilities


Describe the use of the src and controls attributes in the <video> element.

SRC is how you would add your Video into the elememt it containts the path that you want to embed. Controls allows the user to control the audio and video playback of the move that you have added to your website. Such as pause,mute audio or skip forward.


Why is it important to have fallback content inside the <video> element?

Some browser might not support your video. So by having a fallback content it allows you to have text in stead of the vid. This then allows screen readers and other users know that there was a video there and what it was of.



